OVERWATCH_CODEX — Section-by-Section Audit
Rating Scale
•	A = Production-ready, well-designed, justified
•	B = Solid but has issues to fix
•	C = Functional but questionable value or has significant problems
•	D = Needs major rework or removal consideration
•	F = Actively harmful or waste
________________________________________
1. DBA Control Room (dba_control_room.py) — B+
Lines: 4,618 | Role: Primary landing page / operational triage
Strengths:
•	Workflow-first design; routes DBAs to specific tools
•	Mart-first with live ACCOUNT_USAGE fallback — correct architecture
•	Lazy imports via _LazyPandas and _lazy_util reduce startup cost
•	Operator briefing pattern is excellent UX for leadership
Weaknesses:
•	4,600 lines is too long. This is 3 files pretending to be 1.
•	Duplicates safe_float, safe_int, get_active_environment from utils (why?)
•	15+ mart SQL builder references makes the dependency graph unclear
•	Button-driven loads on every pane — fine, but the pane enum is 15+ items
Recommendation: Split into dba_control_room_shell.py (routing/layout, <200 lines) + dba_control_room_panes/ directory. Already has dba_control_room_shell.py as a separate file — finish the split.
