2. Cost Center (cost_center.py) — B
Lines: 3,155 | Role: Credit attribution, chargeback, forecast
Strengths:
•	10 well-defined views covering the full FinOps lifecycle
•	Company/environment filtering consistently applied
•	Mart-first with fallback — good cost isolation
•	Chargeback logic uses get_company_case_expr() from company_filter — correct
Weaknesses:
•	Also too long (3,155 lines) — 10 views in one file is unmanageable
•	"Forecast" view is just linear projection from recent burn — could mislead executives
•	"Attribution" and "Chargeback" overlap heavily; users won't know which to use
•	No cost-per-section breakdown visible to the user
Recommendation:
•	Split into cost_center/ with one file per view
•	Merge "Attribution" and "Chargeback" into a single "Cost Allocation" view
•	Add confidence labels to Forecast (you have the metric_confidence_label helper — use it)
