5. Live Monitor (live_monitor.py) — B-
Lines: 472 | Role: Real-time query monitoring
Strengths:
•	Uses @st.fragment(run_every=N) correctly — non-blocking auto-refresh
•	INFORMATION_SCHEMA → ACCOUNT_USAGE fallback is thoughtful
•	Timeline and Sessions sub-views add forensic depth
Weaknesses:
•	SQL injection at line 112 (status_filter in f-string) — CRITICAL
•	Auto-refresh bypasses the tiered cache — burns credits continuously
•	filter_existing_columns probes fire inside the fragment on every refresh cycle
•	No "stop all" kill switch if a user leaves the tab open
Recommendation:
•	Fix injection immediately (P0)
•	Route fragment queries through run_query(tier="live") — gets 30s caching for free
•	Move filter_existing_columns outside the fragment (it's metadata, won't change intra-session)
